\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Nefesh - Every creating thing in the world has a Nefesh, the G-dly force that gives it life. Inanimate objects (such as rocks) have only this. (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://books.google.com/books?ei=PHs_TsYqjrm2B537rfUM&ct=result&id=oMluAAAAMAAJ&dq=wisdom%20understanding%20knowledge%20boteach&q=nefesh#search_anchor"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0 see here}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 )}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Ruach - Every living thing has a Ruach as well, the life-giving force that animates the living thing. (see\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://books.google.com/books?ei=PHs_TsYqjrm2B537rfUM&ct=result&id=oMluAAAAMAAJ&dq=wisdom%20understanding%20knowledge%20boteach&q=ruah#search_anchor"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0 here}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 )}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Neshamah - Referred to in Tanya as "an actual part of G-d". This is only found in the Jew. (see\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://books.google.com/books?ei=PHs_TsYqjrm2B537rfUM&ct=result&id=oMluAAAAMAAJ&dq=wisdom%20understanding%20knowledge%20boteach&q=neshamah#search_anchor"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0 here}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 )}
