\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The Maharsha in his\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://hebrewbooks.org/pdfpager.aspx?req=37952&pgnum=266"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Chidushe Aggadot (Berachot 3A, d"h\~{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 "Mishmorah Rishonah Chamor"}}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ) says almost the exact same thing. He says that there are 3 parts of the soul of man which are called "The Natural", "The Life", and "The Intellect". He says that Kabbalists call them the "Nefesh", "Ruach", and "Neshamah". See there for a little more elaboration.}
