\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Tanya posits that all humans possess a\~}{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 nefesh bahamit}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \~("animalistic soul") whereas only Jews possess a\~}{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 nefesh elokit}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \~("G-dly soul"), whatever that means. But there are other opinions.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Rabbi Balk consulted several major rabbis, all of them affiliated with the Beth Din of America, regarding the question: "do Jews have entirely different souls than non-Jews?"}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sb180\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 One rabbi replied: "of course, what's the question?"}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Another replied: "Of course not, what are you talking about?"}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sa180\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A third replied: "Believe it if you like, not if you don't; it's not one of Maimonides' Thirteen Fundamentals."}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 I don't think there is a conflict. Each human has a\~}{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 neshama}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , however, Jews have two\~}{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 neshamot}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \~- one that all the nations have, and an extra one that only Jews have. Additionally, there is a third\~}{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 neshama}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \~that only Jews Receive on shabbat.}
